Reasoning: The paper deals with the complexity of algorithmic problems for matrices represented by MTDDs, which are a type of data structure used in computer science. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of matrix operations, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of MTDDs in representing matrices also has applications in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also touches on the topic of symbolic computation, which is related to scientific computing (cs.SC). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of computing determinants and specific entries in matrix products, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
